    "scope": "D3",
    "claim_type": "definition",
    "status": "active",
    "claim": "MAC (Mandatory Access Control) is an access model in which the system enforces access by comparing classification labels; owner cannot override. Used in high-security environments (e.g., military systems) where data sensitivity labels drive all access decisions.",
